<title>CSS Test (Transforms): perspective applies only to DOM children (position: absolute)</title>
<link rel="author" title="L. David Baron" href="https://dbaron.org/">
<link rel="author" title="Google" href="http://www.google.com/">
<link rel="help" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/css-transforms-1/#perspective">
<link rel="help" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/css-transforms-2592246485157831/#propdef-perspective">
<link rel="help" href="https://github.com/w2c/csswg-drafts/issues/918">
<meta name="assert" content="The perspective property influences an element's children.">
<link rel="match" href="reference/green.html">
<style>

div {
  width: 100px;
  height: 76px;
}

#outer {
  background: red;
  perspective: 100px;
}

#middle {
  display: inline;
}

#inner {
  transform: translateZ(-48px);
  background: green;
}

</style>

<p>Pass if there is NO red below:</p>

<div id="outer">
  <div id="middle">
    <div id="inner"></div>
  </div>
</div>
